Some experts question whether the verdict will stand up to further appeals, while others highlight the legal complexities of the case and the challenges of achieving convictions in sexual assault cases. The court's ruling is seen as a setback for the #MeToo movement, raising concerns about the ability of victims to hold powerful individuals accountable. However, opinions vary on the fairness of the overturned conviction, with some arguing that it represents a miscarriage of justice while others believe the court made the correct decision based on legal technicalities.

name: Bell's palsy
summary: Philadelphia 76ers star center Joel Embiid has been diagnosed with Bell's palsy, a condition that causes facial paralysis. Embiid revealed his diagnosis after scoring a career-playoff high of 50 points in Game 3 of the Eastern Conference semifinals against the Miami Heat. Bell's palsy is a temporary condition that usually affects one side of the face, causing weakness or paralysis of the facial muscles. Symptoms can include drooping eyelids, an inability to smile or close one eye, and difficulty speaking or eating. The exact cause of Bell's palsy is unknown, but it is thought to be caused by a viral infection or inflammation of the facial nerve. In most cases, symptoms resolve within a few weeks to months, but some people may experience permanent weakness or paralysis.
